algorithms.paths

Class DP_Solution_Iterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • algorithms.paths.DP_Solution_Iterator

  • public class DP_Solution_Iterator
extends Object
    An UNranked enumeration algorithm for a DP problem specified by a DP_Problem_Instance object. It is implemented as an iterator that is first initialized and then the method get_next() returns the next DP solution in an arbitrary order. Unranked enumeration is implemented as a Lawler procedure without any PQs, thus yielding constant delay (if the number of stages is constant). IMPORTANT: Before using this class, DP_Problem_Instance.bottom_up() must have already been run on the DP instance.
    Author:
    Nikolaos Tziavelis

      • latest_solution

        protected DP_Prefix_Solution latest_solution
        Stores the solution returned in the previous call of get_next(). This is required because candidates generated from the k'th solution are found and inserted into the list in the (k+1)'th call.

      • latest_sidetrack_stage

        protected int latest_sidetrack_stage
        The stage in which latest_solution made a sidetrack (by going to a successor). It is the same as the length of the prefix that we popped in the previous call of get_next(), that was then expanded to latest_solution. By convention, latest_sidetrack_stage of the top-1 solution is 1.
